product_name: LancomeSkin Idole 3 Serum Supertint Skin Tint
summary: SummaryLancôme's Skin Idôle 3 Serum Supertint Skin Tint covers like a tint yet feels like a serum, delivering a luminous natural finish for up to 24H. This tinted serum offers lightweight, buildable coverage that seamlessly glides on skin.
details: DetailsBenefitsInstantly blurs, evens & hydrates skin for a dewy, healthy-looking complexion that lasts all daySkincare-infused formula reinforces your skin barrier with 3 powerful serums: Niacinamide, Hyaluronic acid & vitamin EKey Ingredients1% Hyaluronic acid instantly hydrates skin2% Niacinamide reinforces skin barrierVitamin E infusedResearch ResultsDelivers up to 24H luminous glow*Instantly smooths & blurs*Controls & reduces shine once applied*Visibly plumps & hydrates skin*Non sticky, non-greasy*Crease-proof, does not settle in wrinkles or fine lines*Non-comedogenic (wont clog pores)*96% agree formula is lightweight & 96% said bare skin looks smoother after 4 weeks*91% agree skin looks naturally refreshed**In a consumer test.Item 2638736How To UseShake well before use.Using Fingers: Use ring finger to apply for a natural finish.Using a Sponge: Use a damp sponge to apply for a dewy finish.Using a Brush: Use a foundation brush to apply for maximum coverage.Pro Tip: To keep your skin tint in place longer, apply a light dusting of Teint Idole Ultra Wear Setting Powder with a fluffy powder brush.IngredientsIsododecane, Dimethicone, Aqua/Water/Eau, Glycerin, Alcohol Denat., Butylene Glycol, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Peg-10 Dimethicone, Perlite, Niacinamide, Silica, Polyglyceryl-10 Laurate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Isopropyl Lauroyl Sarcosinate, Diisopropyl Sebacate, Glycine Soja Oil/Soybean Oil, Tin Oxide, Dipentaerythrityl Tetrahydroxystearate/Tetraisostearate, Silica Silylate, Kaolin, Aluminum Hydroxide, Magnesium Sulfate, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Bis-Peg/Ppg-14/14 Dimethicone, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Ethylhexyl Hydroxystearate, Tocopherol, Phenoxyethanol, Parfum/Fragrance.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Shake well before use.Using Fingers: Use ring finger to apply for a natural finish.Using a Sponge: Use a damp sponge to apply for a dewy finish.Using a Brush: Use a foundation brush to apply for maximum coverage.Pro Tip: To keep your skin tint in place longer, apply a light dusting of Teint Idole Ultra Wear Setting Powder with a fluffy powder brush.

reviews.headline: Skin Idole 3 Serum Supertint
reviews.comments: This product is easy to apply and goes on smoothly for coverage and long lasting hydration. The packaging is easy to open to access the product. The product bottle is easy to open and dispense the right amount of tinted serum needed for the individual using it for coverage. I love the fresh glow finish it provides along with breathable texture and lasting hydration. It definitely improved the smoothness of my skin. Would definitely recommend this product for lasting, breathable foundation coverage. I happen to love Lancome products.

reviews.headline: Blends easily
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I like the bottle of this foundation. The ability to squeeze it seems like it will make getting every last drop easy. In my opinion it was a bit heavier than it should have been for a skin tint, so for me it will be better suited for winter months, though still lighter than a foundation. It blended easily and I saw no oxidation.

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again in my right shade
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love the packaging and the finish was nice. I think I need another shade though. Coverage was nice as well. I'd buy if I got my right shade. Smelled good as well.

reviews.headline: Great Supertint
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. The Lancome Skin Idole 3 Serum Supertint is really light on the skin and gives a nice glow. The bottle is also really nice, especially the dropper which helps with precise application. It also allows for buildable coverage and blends smoothly.

reviews.headline: Great for everyday use!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This tinted foundation offered a smooth, lightweight finish that enhanced natural beauty while providing buildable coverage. It blended seamlessly into the skin, leaving a radiant, healthy glow without feeling heavy or cakey. The formula is hydrating, long-lasting, and ideal for everyday wear. Great shade range, too!

reviews.headline: Powdery finish, non-comedogenic
reviews.comments:
This Lancôme Skin Idôle 3 Serum Supertint feels like a lightweight serum that blurs seamlessly into the skin. It includes isododecane and Alcohol Denat., both of which evaporate quickly—leaving behind a smooth, almost powder-like texture as the pigment sinks in.

Despite containing fragrance, the tint is non-comedogenic and features niacinamide, hyaluronic acid, and vitamin E, all known for their skin-friendly benefits such as hydration, barrier support, brightening, and antioxidant protection—making it a skin-conscious choice even for acne-prone users.

reviews.headline: Light & glowy coverage
reviews.comments: The Lancôme super tint leaves my skin with a sheer glowy finish.  The coverage is good enough to use on it's own for hot summer day if you'll be in air conditioning and just want to even your skin slightly. My only criticism would be that it doesn't hold up as well in hot, humid weather. I was hopeful since it is a serum and a tint that it would be light enough to get through the day without tinted sweat running down my face.  But it doesn't feel heavy and hopefully I'll find a better holding spray to get me through the end of the summer.  I haven't really noticed any of the skin care effects yet but I haven't been using it that long.

reviews.headline: I will be buying again!
reviews.comments: Very lightweight which is what I wanted, and does cover what is needed. Matches me perfect.

reviews.headline: I would buy again
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] 
I am so impressed with the Lancôme Idôle Tint Serum Foundation! From the first application, I could tell this was something special. It gives my skin a natural, radiant finish that looks like my skin—just smoother and more even. The lightweight serum texture feels hydrating and breathable, but still gives surprisingly good coverage. It evens out my complexion without ever feeling heavy or cakey.

I also love that it's infused with skin-loving ingredients, so I feel like I'm getting both makeup and skincare benefits in one. It wears beautifully all day and gives me that healthy, glowy look I've been wanting. Total win for anyone looking for a foundation that's clean, comfortable, and actually improves your skin over time.

Highly recommend if you're looking for something that makes your skin look effortlessly flawless!

reviews.headline: Love love love
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I got so much compliments saying that my skin looks really good. I said it was the foundation that made it look fabulous! It's so easy to use, I didn't have a brush or makeup sponge. I just used it straight out of the bottle. It was nice to be able to squeeze the product and apply it to the skin. No scent to it really. I love the shimmer and glow it gives.

reviews.headline: Worth a try!
reviews.comments: I really enjoyed using this skin tint. It's lightweight, applies smoothly, and feels great on the skin. There's a subtle fragrance, but it's not overpowering and fades quickly. I highly recommend it for those looking for light, everyday coverage. I don't have much scarring or hyperpigmentation, so I can't speak to how well it performs for full coverage needs—but for a natural, effortless look, this is a great option.

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I was excited to try the new Lancôme 3-in-1 Tint Serum. Unfortunately, the shade I purchased (34W) didn't match my complexion, so I wasn't able to wear it on my face. That said, I still wanted to share my thoughts based on packaging, texture, scent, and coverage from my swatch experience.

Packaging:
The serum arrived in a beautiful box, which made a nice first impression. However, the bottle itself didn't live up to my expectations. The cap was confusing to open and remained difficult to remove even after I figured it out. It just didn't feel as polished or elegant as I'd expect from Lancôme.

Scent:
One thing that really stood out to me was the scent which is extremely strong. After swatching it on my hand, I could still smell it hours later. It's a very floral fragrance, so if you love bold, perfume-like scents in your makeup, this might appeal to you. But if you're sensitive to fragrance or prefer unscented or lightly-scented products, this could be a dealbreaker. Personally, I found it overpowering.

Texture & Coverage:
From my swatch, the texture is very lightweight and fluid, which is ideal for those who dislike the feeling of heavy foundation. The formula appears to offer light to medium coverage. It's sheer enough to let skin show through while still providing some evening out to the skin. I also noticed a subtle shimmer that gave my skin a soft, healthy glow. It looked beautiful on the back of my hand, and I imagine it would create a radiant finish on the face as well.

Value:
The bottle is on the smaller side for the price point, so I wouldn't consider this an everyday product. It feels more like something you'd reserve for special occasions or minimal use days.

Final Thoughts:
Although the shade didn't work for me, the product itself seems promising for those who want a sheer, glowy base with a noticeable scent. I'd suggest sampling it in store first, especially if you're sensitive to fragrance or need a more substantial amount of product for daily wear.
faceoff_positive.headline: Beautiful foundation, but packaging needs work

faceoff_negative.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Sadly, after a couple weeks of trying this one out, it's a no for me. Immediately, the shade looked ashy and just kinda lifeless on my skin. It didn't add any dimension at all. I had to layer blush, contour, and concealer just to look alive. And somehow, it still managed to be too drying for my very oily skin, which is saying something. It clung to everything and made my face look patchy within an hour.

The fragrance is extremely irritating, causing my eyes to start burning and tearing up upon application. On top of that, I broke out. Also, claiming three-shade flexibility is unrealistic, especially for those of us with darker skin tones. The undertones aren't even remotely forgiving enough to do that; plus, with how ashy it made me look with my warm undertone, I'd think this was mineral sunscreen or something. 

I'll give it some points: A little goes a long way, plus the squeezable bottle makes it easy to apply, but that's about it. The price point to quality scoring is a complete mismatch. I wouldn't at all recommend it in it's current iteration; it needs to be completely revamped to be wearable, imo.

 2 stars 🌟
